Xinhua Commentary: Turn outstanding returning migrant workers into a new force for rural revitalization-Xinhuanet
Talents are the key to rural revitalization.
Where to find talent?
The group of outstanding returning migrant workers is an indispensable new force.
Xinhua News Agency Fa Shang Hai Chun
Xinhua News Agency, Chengdu, July 26: Turning outstanding returning migrant workers into a new force for rural revitalization
Zhang Xiong, 34, lives in Orchard Village, Meishan City, Sichuan. In 2010, he quit his job in Beijing with a monthly salary of tens of thousands and returned home to start a business.
After several years of hard work, the grape-growing family farm he runs now has an annual income of more than one million yuan, has become a well-known leader in getting rich, and has also been selected into the village " two committees " team.
In recent years, inspired by a series of policies to support agriculture and benefit agriculture, such as national poverty alleviation and rural revitalization, more and more outstanding migrant workers like Zhang Xiong have chosen to return home to start their own businesses, activating a pool of spring water in the countryside.
Sichuan, a populous province in western China and a major labor-exporting province, has implemented the " Excellent Migrant Workers Return Training Project " according to the situation. In 2019 alone, more than 8,000 village party branch secretaries were generated from the outstanding migrant workers, 61,000 village reserve forces were trained, and more than 20,000 party members were developed, providing a strong guarantee for winning the fight against poverty and implementing the rural revitalization strategy.
Well-off is not well-off, the key depends on the villagers.
Since the reform and opening up, a large number of young and middle-aged workers in China's rural areas have gone out to work to increase their income, and some have set up their own enterprises through hard work.
However, objectively, it also leads to the emergence of " hollowing out " in rural areas to varying degrees, especially the weakening of rural grass-roots organizations, and the secretaries of village party branches and party members show the characteristics of " one old and one low, " that is, aging, low education, weak leadership of village party organizations, and outstanding problems.
If rural talents and other factors have been flowing one way to the city, and the countryside has been in a state of " blood loss " and " anemia " for a long time, revitalization is an empty word.
Attracting those migrant workers who are capable, conscious and interested in serving their hometown back, guiding them to return home and start businesses to become rich leaders, training them to become party members and village cadres on the basis of merit, and enriching the ranks of grass-roots cadres is a solution to the root causes of the problem of rural party members and grass-roots party organizations.
Excellent migrant workers can be brought back, and they should be allowed to stay and do a good job.
In recent years, Sichuan has started by paying close attention to the party building of migrant workers, and on the basis of strict selection criteria, established institutional mechanisms such as targeted referral, service guarantee, training and ability enhancement, selection and use of outstanding migrant workers, so that they can improve their ability, have security in work, have hope in life, truly take root in rural areas, and have a sense of accomplishment in starting a business.
This year is the final year of the decisive battle against poverty. Talent is the key factor in the connection between poverty alleviation and rural revitalization.
Party committees and governments at all levels should attach great importance to the group of outstanding returning migrant workers, and through comprehensive measures, turn them into a task force and new force that can stay, fight and cannot be taken away, so as to provide strong organizational guarantee and talent support for rural poverty alleviation, well-off development and revitalization.
