Beijing's natural ecology continues to improve, attracting more than 500 species of wild animals to " settle " in the city-Chinanews.com
2020-07-26 05: 03: 17 Source: Beijing Youth Daily Author: Wang Sishuo Editor: Wang Sishuo
The natural ecology of the capital continues to improve to attract wildlife cities to " settle down "
There are more than 500 species of wild animals in Beijing
(Reporter Wang Bin) Beijing Youth Daily reporter learned from the Municipal Bureau of Landscape and Greening that in recent years, with the continuous improvement of the natural ecological environment of the capital, the species and number of wild animals have also continued to increase.
At present, the number of terrestrial vertebrate wild animals living in Beijing has increased to more than 500 species, including national-level protected animals such as brown horse chicken and black stork, as well as national-level protected animals such as gazelle, swan, grey crane and mandarin duck.
Whether planted in urban forests everywhere in the Second Ring, or embedded in small and micro wetlands between buildings, it not only brings the wild interest of nature to the citizens of the capital, but also attracts wild animals to " settle " in the city.
In midsummer, the Songshan National Nature Reserve, located in the Yanshan Mountains in the northwest of Yanqing District, is full of vitality.
A raccoon was playing leisurely by the mountain stream, while two badgers were fighting with each other.
Looking back, a wild boar couldn't resist the " scratch " on his body and was rubbing hard against the bark. Hu Qiaoli, director of the Songshan National Nature Reserve Management Office, said that as of the end of 2019, there were 178 species of wild animals living in this green sea with a total area of more than 6,200 hectares, including the national protected animal golden eagle and the national protected animal spoon chicken and gazelle. Nearly one third of the city's wild animal species can be seen here.
" In Songshan, wild animals are the real' masters', and our staff can only be regarded as people's' bodyguards' at best. "
Hu Qiaoli said that in order to understand the situation of wildlife in the reserve on the ground, more than 30 professional patrol members patrol along 16 carefully formulated protection routes every day, and there will be a " big circle " every month, which takes a whole day to travel almost throughout the reserve.
" During the inspection, we should not only check and record biodiversity, but also check and install artificial bird nests, rescue injured wild animals, install field infrared cameras and so on. "
More than 200 infrared cameras have been installed in Songshan National Nature Reserve to record the living conditions of wild animals in the forest.
Hu Qiaoli introduced that with the continuous enrichment of biodiversity in the reserve in recent years, more and more wild animals appear in the camera, leopard cats, raccoons and badgers have become " permanent guests, " and the " appearance rate " of the national second-class protected animal gazelle is also increasing.
Zhang Zhiming, Director of the Wildlife and Wetland Protection Division of the Beijing Bureau of Landscape and Greening, said that the number of terrestrial vertebrate wild animals in Beijing has increased from 461 in 1994 to more than 500 now, and the species and number of wild animals in Beijing have continued to increase in recent years.
The presence of wild animals in cities is becoming more and more common, which is closely related to the continuous upgrading of urban greening in the capital in recent years.
In particular, the new round of afforestation and greening construction of one million mu, which began in 2018, proposes to reshape the urban ecological environment, improve the ecological function of forestland and green areas, and highlight the concept of " near nature. "
The planning strives to achieve interconnection and interaction with the surrounding green areas, so as to facilitate wild animals to " visit relatives and friends. " The trees planted are also honey and food plants that animals love.
Black land " planted " agricultural modernization-Xinhuanet
Xinhua News Agency, Harbin, July 26, Topic: Black land " grows " agricultural modernization
In midsummer, two spraying planes passed the million mu high-yield demonstration field in the second operation station of the fifth management area of Friendship Farm, forming two white lines. The words " the first field in the world " planted with black rice seedlings in the green field are particularly striking.
Kong Lingqiang, the headmaster of this operation station, said that this kind of aircraft can spray more than 6000 mu of arable land a day, the efficiency is about 8 times that of drones and hundreds of times that of humans.
This farm is located in Friendship County, Heilongjiang Province, the largest grain-producing province in China. From the sound of rice cutting in the past to the sound of " rumbling " today, Chinese traditional farming and farms have transformed in this black soil belt.
In addition to aircraft, satellites are also used in the modern agricultural production of Friendship Farm.
Kong Lingqiang introduced that, on the one hand, they use satellite remote sensing technology to achieve accurate fertilization, reduce agricultural input and reduce pollution; on the other hand, satellite navigation technology can improve the standardized operation level of agricultural machinery in the field.
In the course of rice production this year, the farm expanded the operating area of satellite navigation unmanned transplanting technology from 3,000 mu last year to 30,000 mu.
This technology makes seedling planting more uniform, maximizes the utilization of sunlight and arable land resources, and saves 16 yuan in labor costs per acre.
Farms have tried new technologies such as informatization and intelligence in agricultural production, forming the largest agricultural machinery group in China from the ground to the sky.
According to statistics, the total number of farm agricultural machinery is 49,000 units (pieces), and the comprehensive mechanization rate in the field is 99.8%.
Agricultural machinery operations achieve 100% GPS satellite navigation, 100% precision seeding in dry fields, and 100% high-power locomotive operations in dry fields.
" Green agriculture, smart agriculture and digital agriculture are the exploring directions of agricultural modernization. "
Liu Hualien, director of Friendship Farm, said.
The key to agricultural modernization lies in scientific and technological progress.
Heilongjiang Agricultural Reclamation, represented by farms, has played a demonstration and leading role in modern large-scale agriculture " aircraft carrier " in recent years, and has initially established a modern agricultural industrial system dominated by large-scale planting, standardized production and industrial management.
On the outskirts of Friendship County, there is an agricultural machinery exhibition park covering an area of 350,000 square meters.
There are more than 140 agricultural machinery (pieces) that have been introduced and used in Heilongjiang agricultural reclamation over the years.
These agricultural machinery and farms have witnessed the development of China's agricultural modernization.
Give up a small family for everyone -- Anhui Hefei Jiangkou River Lianwei mass transfer hit-Xinhuanet
Xinhua News Agency, Hefei, July 26
Xinhua News Agency reporters Chen Shangying, Wang Liwu, Liu Xia Village
At 4: 00 p.m. on July 25, Fu Kunbao, wearing mud-covered rubber shoes, went from the front room to the back room, and his wife Zhou Yan was busy packing things back and forth.
" When I received a call from the village cadre to transfer, I was still gathering grass in the field. "
Fu Kunbao said that he has transferred more than 60 mu of land and planted rice. At present, he is growing well. " I took medicine yesterday, and the tools have not been cleaned up. "
Fu Kunbao pointed to the pesticide sprayer placed in the corner. " No one wants their home to be flooded. Give up their small home for everyone. "
In order to cope with the continuous high water level pressure of Chaohu Lake and possible heavy rainfall, Hefei City, Anhui Province, is preparing to use the Jiangkou River Lianlian flood diversion water storage where Fu Kunbao's family is located on the 26th.
Jiangkou River Lianwei is located in Feixi County, adjacent to the Chaohu dike.
There are thousands of villagers involved in Yandian Township and Sanhe Town in Wei who need to be transferred.
As of 16: 00 on the 25th, the water level of Chaohu Lake, the fifth largest freshwater lake in China, remained at a high level of 13.2 meters, exceeding the guaranteed water level by 0.7 meters.
Fu Kunbao's kitchen was clean, with a pot of pumpkin head vegetables on the table, eggs and some brine in the refrigerator.
" I didn't expect to move. The water in Jiangkou River looks good at present. "
Zhou Yan said that the home is a bungalow, and some large objects have not yet decided where to put them.
" Pack up the valuable items first, and large items such as refrigerators and televisions can be temporarily placed in the homes of neighbors or relatives on high ground. "
Wang Lizhen, a village cadre, gave Fu Kunbao advice.
Wang Lizhen is responsible for the transfer and resettlement of 13 villagers, one household to notify, confirm each person's resettlement plan.
The nearest settlement to Fu Kunbao's home is Su Xiaoxue, Yandian Township, about 2 kilometers away.
In addition to the large items, Fu Kunbao and his wife also have a headache of more than 1,000 kilograms of grain and some newly bought furniture.
" The grain is ready to be dragged to relatives' homes, and the furniture can't be moved. "
After a discussion, the couple put a stool under the newly bought bed and raised the bed by about half a meter.
At 6 p.m., Fu Kunbao began to use a tricycle to transport things to relatives' homes, and Zhou Yan continued to clean up at home.
At 11 o'clock in the evening, the couple looked back and forth at home, pulled the switch and prepared to go to the resettlement site.
" I hope the water will recede early. "
Fu Kunbao said.
At 9: 30 a.m. on July 26, the reporter saw at the scene of Jiangkou River Lianwei that the local area had made all preparations before flood diversion.
