Church fire in Nantes, France: Parish volunteers admit arson is usually kind and reticent-Chinanews.com
China News Service, July 26 (Xinhua) According to foreign media reports, on July 18, the famous Cathedral of St. Peter and St. Paul, a treasure of religious and historical buildings in Nantes, France, was severely damaged in a fire, and the large organ was completely destroyed.
On the 26th local time, the Nantes prosecutor announced that a parish volunteer responsible for protecting the cathedral had been charged with " arson and destruction. "
He has admitted that he lit the fire in the church.
According to the report, local prosecutor Senas said that the 39-year-old parish volunteer from Rwanda admitted that he set fire to three places in the cathedral at night.
The man's lawyer said the arsonist now regretted doing such a thing.
This person entered France through the way of asylum a few years ago, was sheltered in the parish where the fire occurred, and was taken in in the church.
The prosecution pointed out that recently, he tried to renew his visa and was talking to the police about it.
But the church said it still couldn't believe that the believer, who was usually very kind, smiling, but not very talkative, would destroy the church he loved so much.
On the day of the fire on July 18, the volunteer had been questioned and investigated by the police because of illogical problems in the narrative, but he was later released.
The picture shows firefighters carrying out rescue at the scene.
On the evening of the 25th, this person was summoned again because professional engineers from the laboratory of the Paris Central Police Department obtained new evidence.
This time, the man admitted to arson.
According to reports, if convicted of intentional arson and destruction, the suspect could face 10 years in prison and a fine of 150,000 euros.
According to the report, the fire caused serious damage to St. Pierre and St. Paul's Cathedral. The organ in the church was completely burned down and the stained glass window behind the organ was also seriously damaged.
Brunet, the chief architect of French historic preservation buildings, believes that it is conservatively estimated that the restoration of Nantes Cathedral will take at least three years.
Comprehensive news: US unilateralism undermines bilateral relations International public opinion supports China's countermeasures against the United States-Xinhuanet
Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, July 26: On the morning of July 24, the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs informed the US Embassy in China that China had decided to revoke the license for the establishment and operation of the US Consulate General in Chengdu and put forward specific requirements for the Consulate General to stop all business and activities.
International public opinion believes that the unilateral measures taken by the United States have caused serious trouble to China-US relations. It is legitimate and necessary for China to respond to the unreasonable provocation of the United States and take countermeasures.
Andrés Bolks, director of the China Research Center of the Institute of International Studies of the University of Chile, said that the unilateral measures of the United States have damaged the bridge of understanding between the two peoples and caused a crisis in the relationship between the two major countries.
China's notification to the United States to close its Consulate General in Chengdu is a countermeasure to the unilateral measures taken by the United States and is in line with diplomatic practice.
Patricio Giusto, a professor at the Catholic University of Argentina and director of the Arab-Chinese Research Center, believes that China's above-mentioned decision is a legitimate and necessary countermeasure to the previous provocation of the United States, not against ordinary Americans.
The United States is trying to pressure China to cover up its weak response to the COVID-19 epidemic and divert the attention of the American people.
Bambang Suryono, chairman of the Asian Innovation Research Center, an Indonesian think tank, said that the provocative diplomatic posture adopted by the United States has caused serious trouble to China-US relations, and bilateral relations are facing serious challenges.
China's notification to the United States to close its Consulate General in Chengdu is a normal countermeasure and is in line with diplomatic practice. It not only reflects China's principled position of resolutely safeguarding its own interests, but also reflects the rationality, advantages and justice of China's diplomacy.
Tanzanian commentator Francis Semwinza said that China's above-mentioned decision is a legitimate and necessary response to the provocation of the United States.
China-US relations should return to normal, and the US should take the initiative to improve its relations with China and stop interfering in China's internal affairs.
The United States should focus on how to achieve win-win results with China economically and politically, and how to benefit the two peoples and the international community as a whole.
Ali Yusuf, executive director of the Sudan-based Federation of Arab-Chinese Friendship Associations, said that the countermeasures China was forced to take were a legitimate and necessary response to the unreasonable actions of the United States, in line with international law and the basic norms of international relations, as well as diplomatic practices.
Earlier, the US request to close the Chinese Consulate General in Houston seriously violated international law and the basic norms of international relations.
We hope that the US side will rescind its previous relevant decisions and create the necessary conditions for bilateral relations to return to normal.
Singapore's Lianhe Zaobao published an editorial saying that the greater strategic intention of the United States is to contain China and prevent China from continuing to rise.
In the face of the step-by-step pressure of the United States, although China is very reluctant to see China-US relations continue to deteriorate, it has to take countermeasures.
