Pursuing the Poetic " Yellow River Dream " -Chinanews.com
(China's Poverty Reduction Story) Pursuing the Poetic " Yellow River Dream "
China News Service, Yinchuan, July 26 (Yang Di) " Jiuqu Yellow River thousands of miles of sand, waves and winds from the horizon. "
The Yellow River, which aroused the pride of countless literati, has given birth to the beautiful and rich Ningxia Plain. Now, Ningxia, which has the reputation of " plugging up the Jiangnan River, " is adhering to the concept of " ecological priority and green development " and pursuing the poetic " Yellow River Dream. "
The " Blue Wave Dream " of River Clear Water Show
" The Yellow River in the world is rich in Ningxia. " The Yellow River flows through Ningxia for 397 kilometers, which is the " mother river " for raising one side.
However, with the rapid advancement of industrialization and urbanization, the development, utilization, management and protection of rivers and lakes are unbalanced, and chaos such as excessive sewage discharge, land surrounding lakes, and encroachment on water areas are highlighted, leading to black and smelly water bodies, excessive water quality, dirty environment and ecological degradation.
Now, Ningxia is promoting the diverse restoration of water ecology and striving to clear the Yellow River.
Water control should start from the source.
In Yinchuan, Ningxia, the local government adopted the method of " raising standards + pollution control + strict management, " all sewage in industrial parks was treated centrally, all urban sewage treatment plants achieved Grade I A standard discharge, and black and smelly water bodies in urban built-up areas were basically eliminated, and the third batch of black and smelly water demonstration cities in China was successfully declared.
In addition, Ningxia fully implemented the river and lake length system in 2017, and now it has achieved full coverage of the five-level river and lake length system in districts, cities, counties and villages, and river and lake length patrol has become the norm.
Gu Jincheng, 64, who lives in a village near the Yellow River, witnessed the changes in the Yellow River: " The water used to smell, but the smell disappeared after remediation. "
Gu Jincheng said that the ecological environment is better and his life is more comfortable. Now he often goes for a walk along the Yellow River with his family to feel the blue water and blue sky.
Sha Gu Xiangji's " Wetland Dream "
Flying birds, green trees, trestle roads, clear water... Fan Zhongyan's beautiful scenery of " Sha Gu Xiangji " has become a reality in the Yellow River Wetland Park in Yinchuan, Ningxia.
The Yellow River flows through Ningxia, and a variety of wetlands such as river wetlands, lake wetlands and swamp wetlands have been formed along the way, which plays an important role in promoting the rational utilization of water resources and water ecological balance, and has also become an important international bird migration channel.
Since 2009, relevant departments in Ningxia have invested about 3.45 billion yuan in wetland protection projects. At present, Yinchuan wetland covers an area of 19,200 hectares, with a wetland protection rate of 78.5%. There are nearly 200 natural lakes and swamp wetlands, with 5 national wetland parks, 1 national urban wetland park, 6 autonomous region-level wetland parks and 8 municipal parks.
Lu Jinhu, deputy director of Yinchuan Wetland Protection Center, told reporters that wetland protection has increased biodiversity, which is particularly evident in birds. " The gull is an endangered bird. There are only more than 20,000 in the world, of which more than 2,000 live in Yinchuan Wetland. "
At the same time, Ningxia has delineated a 500-meter red line for the wetland protection area on both sides of the Yinchuan section of the Yellow River in accordance with the law, stipulating that no unit or individual may carry out development, construction and business activities within the scope of protection except for public welfare projects.
Zhao Shaoyong, deputy director of Yinchuan Water Conservancy Service Center, said that through the treatment of pollution sources, the comprehensive improvement of river and lake ecology and the construction of terminal wetlands, the water quality of the nine main yellow drainage ditches in Ningxia has reached 100% of the Class IV standard. " Now the water is clear, the fish swim and the flowers bloom. "
Pu Huimin's " Drinking Water Dream "
Yinchuan City, Ningxia, once had an " awkward " title: the only city along the Yellow River that " guards the Yellow River and lacks water to drink. "
Since 2010, Yinchuan City has been facing the problem of persistent water shortage at the peak of summer. The " pain of water shortage " in the past ten years has become a painful summer experience for many high-rise residents. However, under the current situation that major water sources are at the limit of overmining and a large area of groundwater overmining funnel area has been formed underground in urban areas, water shortage has become a difficult problem for Yinchuan City.
Thanks to the improvement of the water quality of the Yellow River, drinking the purified Yellow River has become a good solution to the drinking water problem of local residents.
Ding Ming, deputy director of Yinchuan Water Bureau, said that in order to improve the living and production water demand of urban and rural residents in Yinchuan, Ningxia launched the water supply project on the western line of urban and rural areas in the Yinchuan metropolitan area in due course, replacing the original underground water source with high-quality Yellow River.
" On December 29, 2019, the water supply project officially provided water to the three districts of Yinchuan City. In 2020, residents of Minning Town and Helan County also drank the Yellow River. "
Ding Ming said that the Yinchuan water conservancy department will give overall consideration to the transformation of the integration of regional rural drinking water and urban water supply. " In the next step, we will integrate all the scattered rural water supply points into the West Line water supply project, and it is expected to basically realize the integrated urban and rural water supply in Yinchuan by the end of this year. "
