In 2020, the governance work will be further strengthened, and on the basis of App verification, the governance scope will be further expanded to SDK (software development toolkit) and small programs.
It is reported that the working group will conduct thematic research and in-depth detection on issues such as irregular collection and use of personal biometric information and abuse of sensitive permissions by App, focusing on background permissions abuse such as recording and taking photos.
According to the circumstances of the problem and the severity of the consequences, the working group will impose penalties such as interviews, warnings, removal from shelves and fines in accordance with laws and regulations, so as to form an effective deterrent to illegal violations.
It is understood that the working group plans to formulate and issue an application store audit management guide for the collection and use of personal information by App, guide and urge app stores to do a good job in the pre-launch audit of App, and strictly close the entrance.
In addition, the working group will also issue free technical tools to guide small and medium-sized enterprises to carry out self-test evaluation, and improve the legal compliance of small and medium-sized enterprises' personal information collection and use activities.
