Interestingly, the " post-90s " tend to start with a small sum of money, and 60% of the average amount of money saved is less than 20 yuan...
Saving money with Yu Bao has also become the saving habit of " post-90s. "
Data show that out of the 700 million Yubao users, 134 million users are " post-90s. "
There are 174 million " post-90s " in China, that is to say, about three out of every four " post-90s " in the country are saving money with Yu Bao.
At present, the 7-day annualized yield of Yuanbao and other monetary funds has fallen to about 1.5% from above 2% at the beginning of the year.
Even so, it did not affect the pace of saving money in the " post-90s. "
Under the background of the promotion of Yuanbao's " saving effect, " many young people who are accustomed to using Yuanbao have also been directly transformed into " basic people. "
Alipay data show that as of July 13, the number of new " basic people " on Alipay has more than doubled year-on-year in the past month, and more and more young people have achieved " advanced " financial management on Alipay.
Some analysts believe that the inflow of funds from Yubao into the stock market is also an important reason for the clear decline in the share of the International Monetary Fund in June.
The report also shows that " post-90s " girls are more likely to save more money, with an average of 20% higher than that of boys. Among the users holding funds on Alipay platform, 60% are men, and women tend to choose a more robust financial management method than men.
After saving money, what are the plans for the " post-90s "?
Alipay data shows that the " post-90s " have the habit of saving money for the goal, and the largest number of users take travel as the goal of saving money.
Affected by the epidemic, many " post-90s " saved money to prepare for travel after the epidemic; the resumption of cinemas also provided a new way to switch from saving money to consumption.
