France increases military investment in space-Xinhuanet
French Defense Minister Florence Paley said on the 24th that France will add hundreds of millions of euros to its space defense budget to develop space military forces to prevent " unfriendly actions " that other countries may carry out in outer space.
Paley told the Provence newspaper on the same day that between 2019 and 2025, the expenditure budget for French space military projects will increase from the previously proposed 3.6 billion euros (about 4.2 billion US dollars) to 4.3 billion euros (5 billion US dollars).
According to the French Military Planning Act 2019-2025 approved by the French Parliament in 2018, France is expected to update its existing observation satellites and communications satellites, launch three electromagnetic listening satellites, and improve the modernization of space surveillance radar.
French President Emmanuel Macron announced in July last year that a space military command and an " aviation and space force " would be established within the French Air Force.
Paley said she will officially announce the establishment of the space force when she visits a military school in Salon, Provence.
Paley said that this space force belongs to the Air Force and will have 500 personnel by 2025.
" People used to think that space serves the common interests of science, and this idea is gone forever. Now space is a place where countries compete for global hegemony, " she said.
Paley reiterated Macron's previous statement, saying that France has no intention of provoking an arms race.
" We are by no means engaged in an arms race, but it is my responsibility to be fully aware of the threats we may face. "
Paley recalled the surveillance of a military satellite shared by France and Italy in 2017.
She said that the " peeping " was a Russian satellite.
Russia denies this claim.
Paley said that France will " soon " have small patrol satellites capable of detecting and locking " the black hands behind those unfriendly actions. "
French media believe that the reason why France seeks to establish a space force is because US President Donald Trump asked the US Department of Defense to draft a bill to establish a space force in February last year.
Trump signed the National Defense Authorization Act last December, approving the establishment of the sixth army of the United States, the Pacific Air Force.
Some experts are concerned that these US measures have accelerated the pace of US space militarization and may trigger a new round of space arms race.
