The report says the shared accommodation market has picked up since March-Chinanews.com
Xinhua News (Reporter Yang Zhaokui) The " China Shared Accommodation Development Report 2020 " (hereinafter referred to as the " Report ") released by the Sharing Economy Research Center of the National Information Center shows that due to the impact of the epidemic, the transaction volume of China's shared accommodation market decreased by 72.1% year-on-year in the first five months of 2020.
However, the shared accommodation market has picked up since March, and the market turnover, order volume and reception number have gradually recovered.
The Report shows that the transaction volume of the shared accommodation market decreased significantly. On the one hand, due to the sharp decline in the demand for travel accommodation under epidemic prevention and control, the number of orders decreased sharply. The total number of orders in the first five months decreased by 65% year-on-year and the number of arrivals decreased by 63% year-on-year. On the other hand, the weak demand also led to a relatively obvious decline in night prices, with the average night price in the first five months falling by 16% year-on-year.
However, the market turnover in March, April and May increased by 78%, 199% and 35% respectively; the number of orders increased by 141%, 152% and 50% respectively; and the number of receptions increased by 81%, 112% and 28% respectively.
The Report points out that the development of the shared accommodation industry has been promising for a long time, but there are still many uncertainties in the near future.
In this regard, Yu Fengxia, deputy director of the Sharing Economy Research Center of the National Information Center, told the reporter of the Workers' Daily that the development of shared accommodation needs stronger policy support. On the one hand, it is necessary to do a good job in the implementation of policies already issued in the early stages, further strengthen policy publicity and focus on creating a better business environment; on the other hand, it is necessary to further strengthen policy guidance and support from stimulating consumer demand, enriching the supply of tourism accommodation services, innovating service methods and strengthening cooperation between the government and platform enterprises.
