Xiamen, China, July 26 (Yang Fushan Zhang Shushan Xu Jingyi) Vascular Surgery of Shanghai Changhai Hospital of Naval Military Medical University, a famous vascular surgery center in China, signed a contract with Vascular Surgery of Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University on the 25th to jointly set up a collaboration center to promote exchanges and cooperation between the two sides in the field of vascular surgery, especially in the field of aortic emergency and severe disease.
Zhongshan Hospital affiliated to Xiamen University said that after the vascular surgery of the two hospitals formally formed a collaborative unit, they will carry out remote consultation, formulate treatment plans with real-time online consultation with Changhai Hospital, select and send talents for further training, and jointly carry out weekly surgical technical exchanges, teaching and room inspection; For complex cases, Changhai experts can be invited to the hospital to perform surgery according to the needs of patients, so that patients in southwest Fujian can enjoy the top medical resources in China without leaving the province.
The two hospitals will also work together to carry out innovative scientific research on surgery, popularization of aortic diseases and early screening, etc.
A special seminar on aorta hosted by Beijing Health Promotion Association and hosted by Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University was held in Xiamen on the same day.
The two well-known hospitals in Shanghai and Xia held the signing ceremony of the Vascular Surgery Collaboration Center at the same time at the meeting, and announced the formation of a collaborative unit to jointly improve the treatment level of vascular surgery-related diseases in southwest Fujian.
The vascular surgery of Shanghai Changhai Hospital is the only institute of vascular surgery in the army and the only clinical medical center for vascular system diseases in Shanghai. It is also the first national key discipline of vascular surgery. It leads the establishment of the professional committee of intra-cavity angiology of the Chinese Physicians Association, and is a top team with deep accumulation in the industry.
Professor Huang Xiaojin, Director of Vascular Surgery of Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University, was interviewed by the media.
Vascular surgery of Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University is the first independent discipline of vascular surgery in Fujian Province. It has long been committed to the diagnosis and treatment of aortic and peripheral vascular diseases. In 2018, it was approved to build a provincial key clinical specialty.
In the treatment of aortic diseases, in addition to the treatment of dissection aneurysms and aortic aneurysms, he has extensive experience in emergency ruptured aortic aneurysms.
" The vascular surgery of Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University is very outstanding in this region in terms of its development history, breadth, difficulty and complexity. Therefore, this time we set up a collaboration center. In addition to aorta, we can also carry out in-depth cooperation in medicine, teaching and scientific research in the diagnosis and treatment of diseases such as lower extremity artery and carotid artery. "
Professor Feng Rui, deputy director of vascular surgery at Shanghai Changhai Hospital, said.
Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University and Shanghai Changhai Hospital signed a contract to establish " Li Zhaoshen Famous Medical Studio " in the Department of Digestive Medicine in 2018.
Professor Huang Xiaojin, director of vascular surgery of the hospital, said in an interview with Xinhua News that the vascular surgery of the hospital has also had a long history of exchanges with Changhai Hospital. This time, the two hospitals formally formed a collaborative unit, bringing the cooperation and exchanges between the two sides to a new level.
He said that the hospital will regularly invite Shanghai experts to Xia to carry out surgical technology exchange, teaching room inspection, difficult case discussion, etc., and further carry out remote consultation. At present, it plans to conduct remote consultation once a week. In addition, the department will also select personnel for further study and exchange to strengthen the training and development of subject talent team.
The reporter learned at the meeting that vascular disease is the leading cause of death in China. As the main road of various organs of the human body, the aorta flows from the heart to the whole body and plays an important role.
The occurrence of aortic diseases is often accompanied by high risk, high mortality and high difficulty of treatment. The thickest section of the aorta is up to 4 cm in diameter. Once a hemangioma is formed, rupture occurs, or vascular endometrial rupture produces dissection, it will cause massive hemorrhage, which is very dangerous.
In recent years, with the change of people's lifestyle and the acceleration of the pace of life, China has become the largest country in the world with hypertension, and aortic diseases have increased. Now, with the development of surgical technology and industrial materials, the treatment of aortic diseases has continued to develop in the direction of minimally invasive, rapid and efficient.
Doctors can properly " change channels " for blood flow by piercing from the thigh and placing a stent in the aorta, so as to avoid the impact on aneurysms or ruptured dissections, and achieve good therapeutic results. Some operations even require local anesthesia.
This academic symposium invited more than a dozen domestic experts to discuss the new progress in the treatment of aortic diseases, and carried out cutting-edge technical training and difficult case discussion in the form of a conference salon.
The reporter learned at the meeting that with the development of surgical technology and industrial materials, the treatment of aortic diseases continues to develop in the direction of minimally invasive, rapid and efficient.
