The longest high-speed railway tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir Area-Zhongxin.com
2020-07-26 17: 34: 48 Source: China News Network Author: Chen Haifeng Editor: Chen Haifeng
The picture shows the construction site of the Small Three Gorges Tunnel.
Photo of China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group
China News Service, Chongqing, July 26 (Reporter Han Lu) The reporter learned from China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Co., Ltd. on the 26th that the Zhengwan High-speed Railway Small Three Gorges Tunnel, with a total length of about 18.9 kilometers, was completed on the same day.
It is understood that the Small Three Gorges Tunnel is not only the longest high-speed railway tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir Area, but also the longest single-hole double-track high-speed railway tunnel with a design speed of 350 km / h among the projects currently under construction in China.
The Zhengwan high-speed railway is located in the three provinces and cities of Henan, Hubei and Chongqing. It connects the Beijing-Guangzhou and Xulan high-speed railway in the north of Zhengzhou, and reaches Chongqing in the south of Wanzhou. It is an important part of the " eight vertical and eight horizontal " high-speed railway network in China.
The Zhengwan High-speed Railway Small Three Gorges Tunnel was completed on the 26th.
The picture shows through the scene.
The Zhengwan high-speed railway starts in Zhengzhou City, Henan Province, and runs southwest through Pingdingshan City, Nanyang City, Xiangyang City, Hubei Province to Wanzhou District, Chongqing. The new line is about 818 kilometers long, with a design speed of 350 kilometers per hour, and about 184 kilometers in Chongqing.
Among them, the Zhengzhou-Xiangyang section has been opened for operation in advance on December 1, 2019, and the Chongqing section is stepping up construction.
The Small Three Gorges Tunnel, which runs through the entire line on the 26th, is a full-line control project of Zhengwan High-speed Railway. The project is located at the junction of Fengjie County and Wushan County in Chongqing, with a total length of about 18.9 kilometers and a maximum buried depth of 890 meters.
Construction of the tunnel began in February 2017 and the entire line was completed on July 26, 2020.
According to Wang Jun, head of Zheng Wan high-speed railway tunnel design of China Railway Second Academy Engineering Group Co., Ltd., the survey and designer, the small three gorges tunnel is located in very complex topography and geological conditions, facing risks such as karst, mud inrush and large deformation of soft rock. It is a Grade I high-risk tunnel, and the design and construction of the tunnel is extremely difficult.
" During the construction of the project, we used geological survey method, geophysical exploration method and advanced drilling method to advance geological prediction, and adopted special design schemes for more than 30 karst caves of various types. For example, a bridge with a length of 24 meters was designed and built to cross a large karst cave with a longitudinal length of more than 10 meters and a depth of more than 55 meters in the tunnel to avoid tunnel settlement, " the Royal Army said.
According to the China Railway Tunnel Bureau, during the construction of the tunnel, the combination of diversion and blocking was adopted. Through the construction of horizontal tunnel guide, grouting to block water, strengthening tunnel structural support and building sewage treatment station, it not only ensured the orderly progress of the project, but also avoided the damage of construction drainage to the water body of the Small Three Gorges Scenic Area. At the same time, it successfully overcome bad geology such as large deformation of soft rock up to 7 kilometers long, and construction problems such as multi-inrush mud inrush with a maximum daily inrush of 157,000 cubic meters.
After the full line of Zhengwan high-speed railway is completed and opened to traffic, it will become a new convenient and fast passenger transport main channel from southwest China to Central Plains, North China and Northeast China, which is of great significance for improving the capacity and quality of northeast railway channels in southwest China, improving the layout of regional road network, accelerating the development of tourism resources and urbanization along the route, promoting coordinated regional development, and promoting the implementation of the western development strategy.
