Since March, pork prices have declined continuously, and the year-on-year increase in food prices fell to 10.6% in May. In June, pork prices rose slightly due to factors such as the slowdown in the number of pigs, the decrease in imports and the recovery of group consumption demand.
The seasonal variation of fresh vegetable prices is obvious, with an average increase of 3.4% in the first half of the year.
Affected by the high comparative base of the same period last year, fresh fruit prices continued to decline year-on-year, with an average decline of 13.3% in the first half of the year.
The basic livelihood of the masses has been effectively guaranteed, and the overall economic and social situation has remained stable and orderly.
With the gradual recovery of transportation and logistics, various places have increased their efforts, and the market supply and demand situation has improved.
Since March, the CPI has declined for four consecutive months, and the year-on-year increase has also fallen from 4.3% in March to 2.5% in June. The overall price level has returned to stability.
In the second half of the year, China's prices will continue to maintain a moderate level, and the overall inflationary pressure is small, but it is still necessary to promote the restoration of production and living order on the premise of normalizing epidemic prevention and control.
Effectively deal with natural disasters such as floods and droughts in major producing areas of grain, fruits and vegetables, strengthen market supervision, and resolutely crack down on acts that disrupt market order such as hoarding and pushing up prices.
