The article said that in the past ten years, China has invested heavily in domestic research and public health construction, which makes China's preparation for COVID-19 much better than that for severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS).
The author said that when SARS broke out in 2002, China was initially ill-prepared, especially the pathogen could not be determined.
When COVID-19 was discovered in December 2019, Chinese scientists were soon able to identify the virus species and shared genome sequencing data with the international community on January 11, 2020.
By the end of January, doctors from mainland China and Hong Kong had clarified the clinical characteristics of the virus and warned the world of the threat of COVID-19 through research papers published in The Lancet.
