China News Service, July 26 (Xinhua) According to the website of the Supreme People's Procuratorate, in the first half of this year, procuratorial organs nationwide prosecuted 58,101 people for fraud crimes, an increase of 35% compared with the previous year.
In particular, among the crimes impeding epidemic prevention and control, fraud crimes are frequent, and the number of fraud crimes prosecuted by procuratorial organs accounts for 43.4% of the total number of crimes impeding epidemic prevention and control.
The Supreme People's Procuratorate has carried out targeted guidance. At present, among the ten batches of typical cases involving epidemic prevention and control, there are a total of 9 cases involving fraud.
Judging from the handling of cases by the procuratorial organs in the first half of the year, there are many names involving fraud crimes, ranging from national macroeconomic policies to people's food, clothing and housing, including epidemic fraud, " medical care " fraud, " health care products " fraud, " enrollment intermediary " fraud, " routine loan " fraud, fraud to defraud state subsidies, fraud to unfreeze national assets, etc., and continue to " promote innovation, " covering education, medical care, employment, old age, social security, land acquisition and demolition, precision poverty alleviation, financial credit and other fields, which not only cause economic losses to the victims, but also seriously affect economic and social development.
In particular, some telecommunications network frauds break through the restrictions of national borders, regions and personnel, and have the characteristics of stakeholder, cross-border, remote and electronic payment. There are many unspecified victims and great harm.
For example, some set up special companies, rent high-end office buildings, set up multiple departments or posts, use legal network platforms to publicize and recruit, train and assess recruiters, and adopt enterprise operation mode management, wearing the " legal cloak, " which is more confusing.
It is incumbent upon the procuratorial organs to punish and prevent crimes in accordance with the law and issue early warning to the public and relevant departments in a timely manner.
In judicial cases, procuratorial organs conscientiously perform their duties, not only adhere to maintaining high pressure on fraud crimes, but also refine various law enforcement measures in a targeted manner, and promote social governance through the production and issuance of procuratorial recommendations.
The procuratorial organs strictly control the facts, evidence, procedure and application of the law in the arrest and prosecution of fraud cases, taking the facts as the basis and the law as the criterion, and doing nothing wrong.
Especially for the crime of telecommunications network fraud, we pay attention to the central role of electronic data in fact determination, and strive to build an evidence chain between electronic data, verbal evidence and documentary evidence.
For example, in response to an epidemic-related fraud handled by the Yinzhou District Procuratorate of Ningbo City, Zhejiang Province, the procuratorate intervened in advance at the first time, and it took only five days from the occurrence of the case to the conclusion, reflecting the attitude and determination to handle it quickly and strictly and maintain the stability of the overall social situation.
In the process of examining arrest and prosecution, we pay attention to the prosecution of missing offenders in cases, correct the omission of 733 arrests by public security organs, and correct the omission of 1,113 co-defendants by public security organs.
In the first half of the year, procuratorial organs nationwide issued 298 procuratorial recommendations on fraud crimes, promoting joint efforts to prevent fraud crimes and promoting in-depth governance.
For example, in view of the loopholes found in the supervision of telecommunications networks by telecommunications enterprises, banks and intermediary organizations in the handling of cases, the People's Procuratorate of Guangzhou City of Guangdong Province and the People's Procuratorate of Dongguan City put forward procuratorial suggestions in a timely manner, urging relevant units to strengthen supervision, improve mechanisms, and promote the construction of long-term systems.
Fourth, make every effort to recover assets and losses.
Procuratorial organs everywhere seize important links such as intervening in investigation, guiding evidence collection, prosecution and prosecution, urge investigative organs to actively recover stolen money, cooperate with relevant departments to do a good job in recovering stolen money and losses, and strive to minimize the economic losses caused by fraud crimes to the people.
For example, the Lin certain routine loan case handled by the Beijing Municipal Procuratorate involved 22 sets of properties waiting to be sealed up. In the case that the property may be disposed of first by other cases, the first creation and issuance of a " Suspension of Execution Letter " was sent to the relevant court in a timely manner. It was suggested that the previous closure court suspend the execution of the property involved, and uniformly dispose of it after the facts of the crime were ascertained, so as to make the best efforts to recover the property involved and recover the losses of the victims.
Prosecutors reminded everyone that they should be very vigilant against fraud crimes, do not expect " pie in the sky, " do not think cheap to be credulous, and keep their own " money bag. "
Yina Town, Weining County, Guizhou Province: Short apple trees widen the road to poverty alleviation-Zhongxin.com
2020-07-26 11: 42: 58 Source: China Economic Network Author: Zhu Yanjing Editor: Zhu Yanjing
In the heat, the reporter of Economic Daily-China Economic Network walked into Zhonghai Village, Yina Town, Weining County, Guizhou Province.
In the hot sun, villager Li Yuanzhong was weeding in the base. Although his face was red, he hummed a few songs from time to time.
Weining County, where Yina Town is located, has a certain reputation in the surrounding areas because of its low latitude, high altitude, abundant light and large temperature difference between day and night. However, because of its small size and many spots, it has not been able to sell a good price and form an industrial scale.
Yina Town used to be a poor township of " Baogu potato for spring and autumn, " and the incidence of local poverty was as high as 25.8% 10 years ago.
In the critical period when poverty alleviation is entering a decisive battle, it is urgent to change traditional planting habits, adjust industrial structure and increase farmers' income.
Chen Chao, the party secretary of Yina Town, and a group of people in the town believed after many visits that industrial development could no longer follow the old path.
To this end, Yina Town introduced leading enterprises and planted apples in a modern way.
Hou Jianwen, deputy general manager of Weining Beyond Agriculture Co., Ltd., came to Yina Town from Shaanxi Province in 2015 to conduct research. He kept an eye on the local planting conditions and began to plant apple trees locally in 2016.
At first, the village mobilized Li Yuanzhong to transfer the land to plant apple trees. Li Yuanzhong and his wife muttered in their hearts: " After planting apples for so many years, they have not seen anyone in the village grow apples and make a fortune. "
" The apples planted are dwarf apples, which will not make the apple tree grow too high. "
What Li Yuanzhong did not expect was that a new method was adopted for apple planting this time. Irrigation pipes were laid under each apple tree, and water and fertilizer were poured to the roots. When the fruit was harvested in autumn, the tractor drove directly into the orchard and could pick the fruit while standing.
At present, the Apple base has gradually entered a high-yield period, and the market is as expected by Hou Jianwen. Apple is not worried about selling and is deeply loved by consumers in Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou and other cities.
The growing apple industry has brought new changes to Li Yuanzhong's life. Although he is still farming, he has a new source of income.
Li Yuanzhong's family has more than 9 acres of land transferred to the Apple Base. Every year, in addition to the guaranteed land transfer fee, there are profit dividends after hanging fruit. The couple usually work in the base. " One person can get 80 yuan a day and have work all year round. "
Li Yuanzhong told reporters that last year's profit dividend earned more than 2,800 yuan, plus the land transfer fee and the couple's working income, the family earned more than 80,000 yuan, " don't worry about food and clothing, and a well-off life has passed. "
" At present, initial results have been achieved. The annual output value of one mu of apples exceeds 15,000 yuan, which is about 10 times that of growing corn. "
Chen Chao told reporters that 20,000 mu of apples have been planted in the whole town of Yina, and there are 6,000 mu in Zhonghai Village alone, covering 4,056 rural households and 17,200 people, including 656 poor households and 2,952 people, and the annual salary is more than 6 million yuan. The base is truly built on the doorstep and there is no need to go out to work.
Li Yuanzhong, whose pockets were bulging, also began to realize his " wish. "
This year's Lunar New Year, Li Yuanzhong bought an off-road vehicle and now drives his car to and from work every day. " There are still more than a dozen acres of land at home. When the next step is to expand the scale of the Apple base, all of it will be transferred to them, and the income will be more. "
Economic Daily-China Economic Network reporter Wu Bingze Niu Jin Wang Xinwei
Membrane separation technology helps crack the " greenhouse effect " -Chinanews.com
Membrane separation technology helps crack the " greenhouse effect "
Schematic diagram of new mixed matrix membrane preparation technology
Our reporter Shang Rui reported: A few days ago, the atmospheric environment and bioenergy team of Tianjin University made significant progress towards " carbon dioxide capture by membrane separation method " and successfully developed a new hybrid matrix membrane preparation technology to greatly improve the carbon dioxide capture performance of membrane materials.
Relevant results have been published as the cover article of the international journal Greenhouse Gases: Science and Technology.
The " greenhouse effect " is a major environmental problem besetting human development, and carbon dioxide emissions are the culprit of the " greenhouse effect. "
How to efficiently capture and utilize carbon dioxide emitted by human beings is the focus of scientists' attention.
" Membrane separation method " is a new carbon dioxide capture technology. It separates carbon dioxide gas with the help of membrane materials. It has the characteristics of high efficiency, energy saving and simple operation.
How to make the membrane material " breathe deeply " and improve the gas separation efficiency is the bottleneck and difficulty of capturing carbon dioxide by membrane separation method.
The scientific research team of Tianjin University innovated ideas and explored the influence of different solvents on the separation performance of membrane gas through repeated experiments.
Experimental results show that using N-methylpyrrolidone as the preparation solvent, the carbon nanotubes in the membrane material are more evenly distributed and " more breathable, " effectively improving the gas separation efficiency and rate of the membrane material.
The carbon dioxide separation performance of the mixed matrix membrane prepared by this new technology is close to the theoretical separation upper limit of this kind of membrane material.
" The new technology provides a new idea for capturing carbon dioxide by membrane separation. "
Li Run, a member of the atmospheric environment and bioenergy team of Tianjin University, said: " We hope that this technology can provide strong support for future coal-fired power plants and chemical enterprises to deal with flue gas and play an important role in controlling greenhouse gas emissions. "
