Understand what is professional grade difference before volunteering to fill in
Every year, some students or parents do not understand the nouns involved in the voluntary application, which affects the voluntary application.
This year, five colleges and universities, Beijing Jiaotong University, Beijing University of Science and Technology, Beijing University of Posts and Telecommunications, Beijing Forestry University and Beijing University of Chemical Technology, jointly issued the 2020 enrollment policy, eliminating the professional grade difference.
What is the meaning of professional grade difference and what is the significance in voluntary filing?
There are three ways of professional allocation rules
Experts remind that before filling in the volunteer, you must read the Admission Regulations of your favorite school in detail and understand the admission rules of colleges and universities, including the transfer ratio, professional allocation rules, etc.
The rules of professional allocation mean that after colleges and universities are transferred, there are three main ways of professional admission: professional priority, score priority and professional grade difference.
The specific method used by colleges and universities will be specified in the Admissions Charter.
However, the admission principle of some colleges and universities is that the total score is preferred, and there is no grade difference between majors.
That is to say, the candidates within the admission range will be queued according to the total score. When the score does not reach the first professional voluntary admission line, it depends on whether the second professional voluntary admission line has been reached, and so on until the last professional volunteer is admitted, and there is no grade difference between the professional volunteers.
The so-called " professional grade difference " means that when colleges and universities arrange candidates' majors, they determine the admission majors of volunteer candidates for different majors according to one or more score values published in the enrollment regulations. This score value is " professional grade difference. "
That is, the score difference between the first professional volunteer and the non-first professional volunteer when colleges and universities admit candidates, and the grade difference between the professional volunteers, such as 3 points, 2 points, 1 point, etc.
For example.
Suppose student Xiaoming applied for A University and scored 560 points. His professional volunteers are: computer, international trade, automation, mechanical engineering, and e-commerce. The professional admission of A University implements the method of professional grade difference, which is divided into 2 points, 1 point, 1 point, and 0 points.
In the professional allocation, if Xiaoming's first major volunteer meets the professional admission requirements and the major has a planned balance, then Xiaoming will be admitted to the " computer " major; if the computer is not admitted, his score will be subtracted by 2 points, and according to the score of 558 points, he will be sorted with the candidates who volunteer for the " international trade " of the first major to determine whether they meet the professional admission conditions; If they still cannot be met, the score will be subtracted by 1 point (i.e. 557 points) for the " automated " admission of the third major volunteer; If they still cannot be met, the score will be subtracted by 1 point (i.e. 556 points) for the admission of the fourth major, and so on.
Different universities have different professional grade difference settings
With the popularization of parallel volunteering, many colleges and universities have abolished the professional grade difference, but some colleges and universities still retain this method this year. Judging from the Admissions Charter published by each university, more than 20 universities have set up the professional grade difference this year.
For example, Sichuan Agricultural University, Shandong University of Science and Technology, Heilongjiang University of Traditional Chinese Medicine, Jiangsu University of Science and Technology, Jiangxi Normal University, Chengdu Medical College, Northeast Electric Power University, Jimei University, Nanjing Medical University, Nanjing University of Technology, Ningxia University, Shandong University of Technology, China Civil Aviation Flight Institute, etc.
In these colleges and universities, each university has a different professional grade difference.
Some colleges and universities have grade differences in each major, such as Ningxia University. Candidates whose files have been submitted to the university are admitted according to the order in which the candidates fill in their professional volunteers.
Some universities have set different professional grade differences between different majors.
For example, at Jimei University, the total score of professional volunteer difference is 4 points, that is, the difference between the first professional volunteer and other professional volunteers is 3 points, there is no difference between other professional volunteers, which is regarded as parallel volunteers, and the professional difference between other professional volunteers and transfer professional volunteers is 1 point.
When filling in the volunteer, candidates and parents must carefully read the admission policy of the reported school to see if there is any professional grade difference and what is the form of grade difference. While fully considering the score, they should also reasonably analyze the school and major to be selected. If the institution clearly adopts the method of score difference in the admission charter, candidates should pay attention to the gradient between the majors when choosing a major to improve the admission probability.
