Establish a special committee for the first time and collectively sign a " long-term plan " for the third Expo Exhibitors Alliance to build a " two-digit link "-Xinhuanet
The first meeting of the Third Expo Exhibitors Alliance was filmed in Shanghai on July 26.
Xinhua News Agency, Shanghai, July 26 (Reporter Zhou Rui) On the 26th, the Third Import Expo Exhibitors Alliance set up a professional committee for the first time here. The first batch of special committees included the Public Health and Epidemic Prevention Special Committee and the Dairy Industry Special Committee. 35 member enterprises also signed a three-year long-term exhibition cooperation memorandum, and the link role of the Expo Exhibitors Alliance has been constantly strengthened.
At the first meeting of the Third Expo Exhibitors Alliance held here on the 26th, Hyundai of Korea, Dow Chemical of the United States, Shiseido of Japan, New Zealand, Siemens of Germany, Michelin of France, and Aslikon of the United Kingdom signed a three-year long-term exhibition cooperation memorandum, and the revised and improved articles of association were also announced for the first time.
The establishment ceremony of the Dairy Industry Professional Committee was filmed in Shanghai on July 26.
According to the latest constitution, the exhibition alliance will introduce the rotation mechanism of the lead unit and strengthen the function of the special committee.
The special committee will put forward suggestions for the analysis of industry development trends and promote the sustainable development of the industry.
At the same time, integrate the resources of the entire industrial chain of the industry, drive associated enterprises to participate in the exhibition with large and small, and build the Expo into a gathering highland for industry enterprises.
The establishment of a special committee on public health and epidemic prevention for the first time is particularly important for the current fight against the COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic.
As the vice chairman of the Public Health and Epidemic Prevention Special Committee of the Third Expo, Qiu Jianping, general manager of Abbott's rapid diagnosis business in Greater China, said that in the next step, Abbott will join hands with more industry partners to explore new solutions and cooperation models to help China and the world fight the COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic.
The establishment ceremony of the public health and epidemic prevention professional committee was filmed in Shanghai on July 26.
It is reported that the third Expo set up a public health and epidemic prevention zone for the first time. Up to now, nearly 50 global enterprises have signed up for the exhibition, with an exhibition area of more than 10,000 square meters.
During the first Expo in 2018, the Expo Exhibitors Alliance was established at the initiative of exhibitors, with the aim of becoming a platform for high-quality exhibitors to exchange and cooperate, a platform for connecting exhibitors to share information and resources, and a think tank platform for promoting economic, trade and business exchanges and development between China and other countries (regions) in the world.
So far, 142 enterprises have joined the Exhibitor Alliance, covering 23 countries and regions around the world.
