Chengdu people gather to watch the US consulate police stop people from " looking too happy "
In response to the US closure of the Chinese Consulate General in Houston, China announced the closure of the US Consulate General in Chengdu on Friday.
On Saturday, the badge of the US consulate was removed, and on Sunday, a dark glass car drove away from the consulate amid boos from passers-by.
On Sunday, many people in Chengdu gathered in front of the US consulate to take pictures. Those who had not been here also came to take a look driven by curiosity about current affairs.
The reporter from Agence France-Presse Chengdu Station also went to observe near the US Consulate in Chengdu, and sent back the news that there was a steady stream of curious people, and many parents took their children for a walk to watch the consulate, take pictures of the building, or take self-portraits.
The consulate was surrounded by guards, and the police " corrected " people's behavior from time to time. They did not seem to allow any unusual behavior: a woman was stopped as soon as she was ready to sing a red song, and a guard confiscated a banner.
But residents of a nearby residential building succeeded in pulling up a giant Chinese flag on their balcony and shouting slogans in support of China.
The US Consulate in Chengdu opened in 1985, covering all consular-related affairs of the United States in southwestern China, especially the Tibet Autonomous Region.
A reporter from Agence France-Presse Chengdu Station said that the Chinese government's response to the United States was relatively restrained: many Chinese people asked the government to close the US consulate in Hong Kong online, but the official only said that " closing the US consulate in Chengdu is a necessary and legal response to the unreasonable behavior of the United States. "
At present, in addition to Chengdu, the United States also has consulates in Guangdong, Shanghai, Shenyang, Wuhan and Hong Kong in China.
Large-scale financial media action " Go to the Village Live to Watch Poverty Alleviation " -Shangbao Network-Shangbao Online
New Hunan Client on July 25 (This reporter) On July 25, the large-scale financial media action " Go to the Village Live to Watch Poverty Alleviation " sponsored by the Financial Program Center of the Central Radio and Television Station started from Xuzhou, Jiangsu Province. Two caravans carrying 5G new media mobile cloud production and broadcasting system slowly drove out of the scene under the eyes of the guests at the scene.
General Secretary Xi Jinping pointed out that " 2020 is a landmark year. We will build a moderately prosperous society in an all-round way and achieve the first 100-year goal. 2020 is also the year of decisive battle against poverty. "
The large-scale financial media action " Go to the Village Live to Watch Poverty Alleviation " is an important measure taken by the Financial Program Center of the Central Radio and Television Station to coordinate with this major theme and do a good job in poverty alleviation publicity.
The action will go into poverty alleviation villages in more than 20 provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central Government, dig fresh poverty alleviation stories, hit the great changes in the appearance of villages, and show how villagers break through the dilemma of survival and development and move towards the road of becoming rich.
The operation will last more than three months.
Starting from Xuzhou, the reporter took the southwest line all the way through Anhui, Hubei, Jiangxi, Hunan, Guangxi, Guizhou, Sichuan, Chongqing, Yunnan, Tibet and other places; the other way took the northwest line through Henan, Shaanxi, Gansu, Qinghai, Xinjiang, Ningxia, Inner Mongolia, Shanxi, Hebei and other places, with a journey of more than 10,000 kilometers.
In the form of reporting, " Go to the Village Live to Watch Poverty Alleviation " is boldly integrated.
The economic development of the villages visited by the caravan will be broadcast through CCTV Financial Channel, Yangguang Economic Voice, China Communications Radio and CCTV Financial New Media.
Among them, the live television broadcast will be mainly completed in the noon news program " World Finance " of CCTV Financial Channel (premiere time: 12: 00-13: 00 from Monday to Sunday), and the golden news program " Economic Information Network " of CCTV Financial Channel will set up a poverty alleviation report column (premiere time: 20: 30-21: 30 from Monday to Sunday).
At the same time, the caravan will broadcast live for up to one hour to each village in the CCTV financial client. By downloading the CCTV financial APP, the audience can watch the live broadcast and participate in the lucky draw.
In terms of technology application and studio design, " Go to the Village Live to Watch Poverty Alleviation " has the courage to make a breakthrough and pioneered the " Outfield New Media Caravan. "
The car is equipped with 5G new media mobile cloud production and broadcasting system, and uses 5G + 4K / 8K + AI technology to realize the organic combination of online and offline, large and small screens, and television broadcasting.
It is equipped with a three-message studio area, which is converted from a container. It is 12 meters long, 2.55 meters wide and 3.98 meters high. The box adopts a hydraulic automatic expansion structure and can be turned up to 120 degrees.
The studio area can also be expanded automatically, and the external expansion platform, with an area of more than 50 square meters, can meet the scene requirements of most programs.
At present, Dongchuan District of Kunming City is already hot in summer, and what is hotter than the weather is the poverty alleviation workshop next to the relocation site.
Lu Ling, an employee of Kunming Esford Electronic Technology Company, said, " Now, as soon as you leave home, you enter the factory to make money and take care of your family, thanks to the free vocational skills training of the trade union organization. "
Walking into the poverty alleviation workshop of electronic components processing in Tongdu Street, Dongchuan District, a busy picture came into view.
Lü Ling, in her 40s, is a single mother who takes care of her children alone and takes care of her elderly parents.
In her most difficult time, the Dongchuan District Federation of Trade Unions helped to come up with ideas and ways to " send coal in the snow " after being busy before running.
Since 2018, Lü Ling has enjoyed assistance policies such as housing, schooling, social security and employment, as well as assistance funds issued by trade unions at all levels.
This year, her child has successfully graduated and employed, and she herself has a job and income after participating in skills training, and was out of poverty at the end of April.
It is reported that the special skills training project of Dongchuan District General Organization to help alleviate poverty is part of the skills training work of Yunnan Provincial Federation of Trade Unions.
In the light of the characteristics of the workers in difficulty in the relocation and resettlement sites for poverty alleviation in the district, the District General Administration conducted an in-depth investigation to understand the training needs and determine the types of training. In the near future, it plans to train a total of 450 electricians, welders, pasta designers, etc.
Recently, Li Yi, an employee of the Menglian County Branch of Agricultural Bank of Yunnan, wrote a sincere thank-you letter to the County Federation of Trade Unions.
In her letter, she sincerely thanked the union for giving her a golden autumn grant from August 2013 to January 2017 to help her complete her studies.
In 2004, Li Yi's father died in a car accident, and her mother was included in the files of workers in difficulty. Since then, she has been enjoying the care of the policy.
With the help of the local trade union, Li Yi successfully completed her studies.
Since 2016, 3,809 households have been lifted out of poverty through institutional guarantees and precise assistance.
The successful relief of Lü Ling's family and Li Yi is a microcosm of the work of Yunnan trade unions to promote the relief of workers in difficulty.
According to Duan Kaiyuan, a staff member of the Legal and Human Rights Work Department of the Yunnan Federation of Trade Unions, the provincial government will strengthen the dynamic management of the files of workers in difficulty, promote the normalization of filing work, and promptly integrate the workers in difficulty who meet the conditions for filing into the assistance system; broaden the application channels for workers in difficulty, and use WeChat to open an online filing service platform for workers in difficulty to facilitate workers in difficulty to declare in a timely manner.
During the epidemic period, it was difficult to go out to work. In order to help workers with difficulties in filing alleviate the pressure of life, Yunnan Province arranged a total of more than 13 million yuan to send warm funds. According to the standard of 2,000 yuan per household for workers with difficulties in filing at the national level and 1,500 yuan per household for workers with difficulties in filing at the provincial level, special warm and condolence activities were implemented for more than 6,000 national and 1,000 provincial workers with difficulties in filing.
At the same time, the provincial head office docks with various Internet recruitment platforms such as social security departments and Zhilian recruitment, pushes recruitment information to workers in difficulty, and provides employment consulting, employment guidance and other services.
